<opener><salute>Viro Illustrissimo et <choice><abbr>Celeberr.<hi rend="sup">o</hi>imo</abbr><expan>Celeberrimo</expan></choice>
<lb/><choice><abbr>Jo:</abbr><expan>Johanni</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-118509969" type="person">Bernoull<choice><orig><g ref="#j">j</g></orig><reg>i</reg></choice></rs> Petrus Antonius <rs key="pers_DE-588-102552517" type="person">Michelotti</rs>
<lb/><abbr>S. P. D.</abbr></salute></opener>
<p><lb/>Quoniam heri <rs key="brieftag" type="letter">Literas</rs><note type="editorial"><!-- heri = gestern bezieht sich auf den Erhalt. Die Angabe 4 huius mensi meint 4. Oktober. --> Von Benedict scheint kein Brief an Niklaus I erhalten. Am 4. Oktober 1719 schreibt allerdings Hieronymus an Niklaus I den Brief mit der Systemnummer 000058996</note> <rs key="pers_DE-588-1089913338" type="person">Fratris</rs> Pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>clarissimi Agnati
         <lb/>Tui <rs key="pers_DE-588-119166895" type="person">Nicolai</rs> istic<!-- orttag --> <choice><abbr>a. d.</abbr><expan>ad diem</expan></choice> 4 hujus mensis datas<add>, atque</add> ad me
         <lb/>perlatas legendo, null<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <add>in iis</add> fuisse fact<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> mentio<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>nem vidi de <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">fasciculo</rs><note type="editorial">Es handelt sich um einen Teil der Dissertation Michelottis, wohl um den ersten Teil, wie er im Brief 000056693 von 1719.09.09 schreibt: "primam dissertationis ... partem".</note>, qu<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> ad Te per <rs key="place_GEO-3173435" type="place">Medio<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>lan<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs> diligentia Tabellarii miss<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> volebam, immo
         <lb/>miss<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> volui ante mens<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice>, et quod superest: et pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice><pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>terea quandoquid<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> a Te Vir <choice><abbr>Illustriss.</abbr><expan>Illustrissime</expan></choice> nullam
         <lb/>ad meas <rs key="B_1719-09-09_991170515151805501" type="letter">litteras</rs><note type="editorial">Michelotti sendet Johann I Bernoulli mit seinem Brief vom 09. September 1719 seine Dissertatio de Separatione Fluidorum in Corpore Animali zur Ansicht und Korrektur. Ferner bittet er im Brief vom 15. September und vom 06. Oktober um sofortige Antwort Bernoullis nach deren Erhalt.</note> responsion<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> accepi, statuo
         <lb/>hac tertia vice ad Te scribere, Teque, uti ali<choice><orig><g ref="#agrav">à</g></orig><reg>a</reg></choice>s
         <lb/>feci, orare ut protinus ad me scribas, mihi<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>que confestim significes <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">fascicul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs><note type="editorial">Es handelt sich vermutlich um den ersten Teil von Michelottis Diss. in Entwurfform (Druck 1721). Vgl. oben.</note> comme<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>morat<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> acceperis nec ne. Nam qu<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> mea
         <lb/><rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">Dissertatio de separatione Fluidor<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> in Cor<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>pore Animali</rs><note type="editorial">Später gedruckt als der Brief: Michelotti, Pietro Antonio, De separatione fluidorum in corpore animali dissertatio physico-mechanico-medica, Venetiis (A. &amp; A. Pinelli) 1721. (Digitalisat [Link: https://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/resolve/display/bsb11219247.html] bei BSB digital)</note>, in illo eod<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">fasciculo</rs><note type="editorial">Es handelt sich vermutlich um den ersten Teil von Michelottis Diss. in Entwurfform (Druck 1721). Vgl. oben.</note> <add>obsignato,</add>
<lb/>et <choice><sic>tella</sic><corr>tela</corr></choice> cerea obducto contineatur, <add>nolo,</add>
<lb/>si Diis placebit, ut evanescat. Spero Te jam
         <lb/>nunc ill<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">fascicul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs><note type="editorial">Es handelt sich vermutlich um den ersten Teil von Michelottis Diss. in Entwurfform (Druck 1721). Vgl. oben.</note> accepisse, qua de re crasti<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>na die <rs key="place_GEO-3173435" type="place">Mediolan<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs> perscrib<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> ad Illustrissi<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>m<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> Marchionissam Loaysam, Butintrochi<!-- persontag -->, 
         <lb/>qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> scripsit, se ill<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">fascicul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs><note type="editorial">Erster Teil der Dissertation. Vgl. Brief von 1719.09.09. Der fertige Druck ist später als dieser Brief: Michelotti, Pietro Antonio, De separatione fluidorum in corpore animali dissertatio physico-mechanico-medica, Venetiis (A. &amp; A. Pinelli) 1721. (Digitalisat [Link: https://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/resolve/display/bsb11219247.html] bei BSB digital)</note> <rs key="place_GEO-3173435" type="place">Mediolano</rs>
<lb/>ad Te misisse. Rogo itaque ut mihi
       <pb facs="1079099" n="2"/>
<lb/>respondeas, sive fascicul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> acceperis, sive non
         <lb/>acceperis. Quod reliqu<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> est quum heri jam
         <lb/><rs key="place_GEO-3171728" type="place">Patavio</rs> discesserit <choice><abbr>Illustriss.</abbr><expan>Illustrissimus</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-119166895" type="person">Agnatus</rs> Tuus istuc
         <lb/>profecturus, mitt<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <rs key="place_GEO-3178829" type="place">Clavenn<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice></rs>, uti jussit, <rs key="brieftag" type="letter">litte<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>ras</rs><note type="editorial"><!-- Recherche ergab: --> Damit ist der Brief, der zu Beginn des vorliegenden Briefes genannt wird, gemeint.</note> quas pro illo accepi.</p> <closer><salute>Tu interim
         <lb/>vale, mihique favere ne dedignare.</salute>
<dateline>Dab<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> 
         <lb/><rs key="place_GEO-3164603" type="place">Venetiis</rs> <choice><abbr>a. d.</abbr><expan>ad diem</expan></choice> <date when="1719-10-13">13 Octobris 1719.</date></dateline></closer>
